"version": "1.0.2",
"title": "5770: abandonment",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5770: abandonment",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The state and experience of being forsaken, shared by God as well as by human beings.</p>\n<h2>God is abandoned</h2>\n<h3>God's people deliberately abandon him</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:13\">JER 2:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:15\">DEU 32:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg2:12\">JDG 2:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs9:9\">1KI 9:9</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr7:22\">2CH 7:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr13:11\">2CH 13:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:4\">ISA 1:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:13\">JER 17:13</a></p>\n<h3>God's people abandon his law</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer9:12-Jer9:14\">JER 9:12–9:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:18\">1KI 18:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr12:1\">2CH 12:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:30\">PSA 89:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:53\">PSA 119:53</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov4:2\">PRO 4:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov4:6\">PRO 4:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:28\">HEB 10:28</a></p>\n<h3>God's people abandon his covenant</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut29:25\">DEU 29:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer22:9\">JER 22:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:32\">JER 31:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan11:30\">DAN 11:30</a></p>\n<h3>God's people abandon his temple</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr24:18\">2CH 24:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr29:6\">2CH 29:6</a></p>\n<h3>Those who abandon the gospel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:1\">1TI 4:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:26\">HEB 10:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:29\">HEB 10:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:4\">REV 2:4</a></p>\n<h2>God abandons those who forsake him</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr24:20\">2CH 24:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num32:15\">NUM 32:15</a> <em>Moses warns the Transjordan tribes</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut31:17\">DEU 31:17</a> <em>Israel's rebellion predicted</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:301\">DEU 32:301</a>SA <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut18:12\">18:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam28:15\">1SA 28:15</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs9:7\">1KI 9:7</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr7:20\">2CH 7:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr28:9\">1CH 28:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:28\">NEH 9:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa2:6\">ISA 2:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer12:7\">JER 12:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam2:7\">LAM 2:7</a></p>\n<h2>God shows mercy to those who have been justly abandoned</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa54:7\">ISA 54:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:19\">NEH 9:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:28\">NEH 9:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:31\">NEH 9:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer51:5\">JER 51:5</a></p>\n<h2>Those who feel abandoned by God</h2>\n<h3>God's people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam5:20\">LAM 5:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:1\">PSA 22:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps43:2\">PSA 43:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps71:11\">PSA 71:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps74:1\">PSA 74:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:38\">PSA 89:38</a></p>\n<h3>Their prayers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps38:21-Ps38:22\">PSA 38:21–38:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:57\">1KI 8:57</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps27:9\">PSA 27:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps71:9\">PSA 71:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps71:18\">PSA 71:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:8\">PSA 119:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer14:9\">JER 14:9</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's feelings of abandonment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:46\">MAT 27:46</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:34\">MRK 15:34</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:1\">PSA 22:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:27\">ACT 2:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps16:10\">PSA 16:10</a></p>\n<h2>God promises never to abandon his people</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut31:8\">DEU 31:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:44\">LEV 26:44</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:31\">DEU 4:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut31:6\">DEU 31:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam12:22\">1SA 12:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:25\">PSA 37:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:28\">PSA 37:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps94:14\">PSA 94:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa49:14-Isa49:16\">ISA 49:14–49:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:20\">MAT 28:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:9\">2CO 4:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:5\">HEB 13:5</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of people who were abandoned</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen16:7-Gen16:8\">GEN 16:7–16:8</a> <em>Hagar</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam30:13\">1SA 30:13</a> <em>a slave</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa49:15\">ISA 49:15</a> <em>a newborn baby</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:3-Ezek16:6\">EZK 16:3–16:6</a> <em>Jerusalem</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:19\">ACT 14:19</a> <em>Paul</em></p>",
